## PROJECT DOCUMENTATION & CONTEXT SYSTEM

This section outlines the standards for project documentation and the context system used by the AI coding assistant.  All documentation must be clear, concise, and easily accessible.

## TECH STACK

This section lists the technologies used in the project.

* **Programming Languages:** Python
* **Formatting:** Ruff (replacing Black, isort)
* **Linting:** Ruff (replacing flake8)
* **Pre-commit hooks:** ruff, ruff-format, trailing-whitespace, end-of-file-fixer, check-yaml, check-toml, debug-statements, mypy


## CODING STANDARDS

This section outlines the coding standards to be followed in the project.  Code must be well-formatted, readable, and maintainable.  Adherence to PEP 8 is expected.  Ruff is the designated formatter and linter.  See the README for usage instructions.


## WORKFLOW & RELEASE RULES

This section details the project's workflow and release processes.  All code changes must be reviewed before merging into the main branch.  Pre-commit hooks should be used to ensure code quality before commits.


## DEBUGGING

This section outlines debugging procedures and best practices.


